# FrogoTV Content Agent

Automatically fill all FrogoTV channels to 24 hours of content by spawning parallel subagents per channel.

Use when the user says "fill content", "content agent", "add content", "fill channels", or "run content agent".

## Overview

This agent queries all channels, calculates how many hours each needs to reach 24h, then spawns one subagent per channel to research and add YouTube videos.

## Steps

### 1. Query current content levels

Use Bash to query Supabase REST API for all channels with their total content duration:

```bash
curl -s 'https://cnnttsihfbyxhzlmzdtv.supabase.co/rest/v1/channels?select=id,slug,name,icon,description' \
  -H "apikey: $NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY"
```

Then query video durations grouped by channel:

```bash
curl -s 'https://cnnttsihfbyxhzlmzdtv.supabase.co/rest/v1/videos?select=channel_id,duration_seconds,position' \
  -H "apikey: $NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY"
```

Calculate per channel:
- `current_hours` = sum of duration_seconds / 3600
- `hours_needed` = 24 - current_hours
- `max_position` = max position value (new videos start after this)

Skip channels that already have >= 24 hours.

### 2. Spawn parallel subagents

For EACH channel that needs content, spawn an Agent subagent **in parallel** (all in a single message with multiple Agent tool calls). Each subagent gets this prompt template:

```
You are a FrogoTV content curator for the "{channel_name}" channel ({channel_icon}).
Channel description: {channel_description}
Channel slug: {channel_slug}

GOAL: Find and add approximately {hours_needed} hours of YouTube videos to this channel.
Current content: {current_hours} hours across {video_count} videos.
Next position number: {next_position}

## How to find videos

Use WebSearch to find high-quality YouTube videos matching this channel's theme.
Search queries should be specific to the channel topic. Try 3-5 different search queries to get variety.

Good search examples:
- "{topic} full lecture youtube"
- "{topic} documentary youtube"
- "{topic} explained youtube 2024 2025"
- "best {topic} youtube videos"

## Video selection criteria

- Prefer videos 10-60 minutes long (longer = fewer needed to fill 24h)
- Educational, well-produced content from established channels
- Mix of lengths: some short (5-15 min), mostly medium-long (20-60 min)
- Avoid: music compilations, ASMR, livestream replays, shorts compilations
- Avoid: videos that are clearly clickbait or low quality
- For kids channels: ensure content is age-appropriate

## For each video found, extract:

- youtube_id (the 11-char ID from the URL, e.g. "dQw4w9WgXcQ")
- title
- duration_seconds (estimate from the displayed duration, e.g. "1:23:45" = 5025s)
- brief description (1 sentence)

## Verify video availability

For each video, check availability via YouTube oEmbed:
```bash
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" "https://www.youtube.com/oembed?url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID"
```
Only include videos that return 200.

## Insert videos into database

Once you have a batch of verified videos, insert them via the Supabase REST API.
Use this pattern for EACH video (increment position for each):

```bash
curl -s -X POST 'https://cnnttsihfbyxhzlmzdtv.supabase.co/rest/v1/videos' \
  -H "apikey: ANON_KEY_HERE" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer SERVICE_ROLE_KEY_HERE" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Prefer: return=minimal" \
  -d '{
    "channel_id": "{channel_id}",
    "youtube_id": "VIDEO_ID",
    "title": "Video Title",
    "description": "Brief description",
    "thumbnail_url": "https://img.youtube.com/vi/VIDEO_ID/maxresdefault.jpg",
    "duration_seconds": 1200,
    "position": {position}
  }'
```

Use these exact keys (read from .env.local in the project root /Users/fotoflo/dev/Frogo2026/.env.local):
- ANON_KEY = value of NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
- SERVICE_ROLE_KEY = value of SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY

## Important

- Track cumulative duration as you add videos. Stop when you've added ~{hours_needed} hours.
- Use ON CONFLICT-safe inserts: add `"on_conflict": "channel_id,youtube_id"` header or just accept 409s gracefully.
- Number positions sequentially starting from {next_position}.
- After inserting all videos, report: channel name, videos added, total hours added.
```

### 3. Collect results

After all subagents complete, summarize:
- Table of channels with: name, videos added, hours added, new total hours
- Any channels that had errors
- Total videos added across all channels

## Environment

Read API keys from `/Users/fotoflo/dev/Frogo2026/.env.local`:
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` — used as apikey header
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` — used as Authorization Bearer token

## Notes

- The schedule system loops playlists, so 24h of unique content means viewers won't see repeats within a day
- Videos are verified via oEmbed before insertion to avoid dead links
- Duplicate youtube_ids per channel are prevented by the DB unique constraint
- New videos appear immediately — the TV picks them up on next channel load
